As has been indicated in the comments, it is quite difficult to grasp exactly what your validation entails. What I understand is that once the value in the input with class ```valtotal``` is greater than 32, a button needs to appear which initializes a modal. You can achieve that with something like this using jquery:

```
$(&quot;.valtotal&quot;).on(&quot;keyup&quot;, function(){
   if($(&quot;.valtotal&quot;).val() &gt;32  ){
      $(&#39;.post-abs&#39;).show();                 
   } else {
      $(&#39;.post-abs&#39;).hide();
   }                
});
```

Similarly, to check whether a particular checkbox has been checked you can do something similar:

```
$(&#39;#theCheckBoxId&#39;).change(function(){
   if($(&#39;#theCheckBoxId&#39;).is(&#39;:checked&#39;)) {
     //Disable the save button
     $(&quot;#saveButtonId&quot;).prop(&quot;disabled&quot;, false);
   } else {
     $(&quot;#saveButtonId&quot;).prop(&quot;disabled&quot;, true);
   }
});
```

If you need a better explanation, try and be more specific regarding your validation

