You need to incorporate content that is dynamically pulled from a spreadsheet
------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Workflow of a possible solution:**

+ Bind your form to a destination spreadsheet (if not already done)
+ Bind a script to to form
+ Withdraw e.g. the row of the last form response
+ Use this value (or modify it as desired) as an incremental Id
+ Incorporate this incremental ID into the title or description of the form
+ Bind a [installable onFormSubmit trigger][1] to your main function


**Sample:**

``` lang:js
function onFormSubmit() {
  var sheet=SpreadsheetApp.openById(&#39;ID OF YOUR DESTINATION SPREADSHEET&#39;).getActiveSheet();
  var lastRow=sheet.getLastRow();
  var id=lastRow-1;
  FormApp.getActiveForm().setDescription(&#39;ID &#39;+id);
}
```
Keep in mind that the change will need some seconds to propagate, the ID might not update directly if the form is submitted with a higher frequency

[1]:https://developers.google.com/apps-script/guides/triggers/installable

